    <field name="scopecontent_teim">Includes a few documents related directly to a CIO-affiliated union's attempt to organize N-YHS's maintenance staff. The bulk of the documents include correspondence with Federal legislators, and their responses, seeking
an amendment from the National Labor Relations Act of 1947 (Taft-Hartley) to exempt charitable, educational, and other organizations to conform
Federal law with that of New York State. The correspondence also includes some exchanges with representatives of other museums concerning their status with unionization efforts. The file includes some print matter, including the House and Senate bills and conference reports, and a summary of the law authored and distributed by U.S. Senator Joseph H. Ball</field>
